This is where being patient with myself comes into play- “You’re a piece of shit” kept nagging in my head since youth whenever I put effort into approaching a woman ending up with a huge zero.. Identifying “automatic thoughts” where in some cases, reality could be sprinkled in or not at all. Depends on how I want to replace the bad thought with a positive one to work through. Breaking down the acronym of PTSD one letter at a time is a test for strength in situations of feeling weak, last night and this morning I felt like an empty void that easily could’ve snapped, but I retraced my steps to prevent myself from going down that path. My therapist said “I’d say you’re pretty resilient, not letting your childhood trauma take over your life.” Took me a while to sit on it in response to if I actually felt that way, slowly I’ll get there.
